{"title_page": "Samir Choughule", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2019}}\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{BLP sources|date=June 2016}}\n{{Notability|biography|date=August 2016}}}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Samir Diwakar Choughule\n| image              = SamirChoughule1.jpg\n| caption            = \n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1973|06|29}}\n| birth_place        = [[Maharashtra]], India\n| yearsactive        = 1993 \u2013 present\n| occupation         = Actor, Writer, Comedian\n}}\n\n'''Samir Diwakar Choughule''' (born 29 June 1973) is an actor and writer from [[Mumbai]], India. Though he is a versatile actor, he is better known for his comedy roles and style. From daily soaps to comedy shows, from theater plays to movies, Samir has acted in [[Marathi language|Marathi]], [[Hindi]] and English shows. He is currently known for his role in \"Maharashtrachi Hasya Jatra\" being telecasted on Sony Marathi.{{citation needed|date=June 2016}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sonyliv.com/details/show/6074325854001/Maharashtrachi-Hasya-Jatra-Vinodacha-Nava-Hangam|title=Maharashtrachi Hasya Jatra|last=|first=|date=|website=Sony LIV|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==Life and career==\nSamir Choughule did his schooling in Shailendra Education Society and later completed his graduation from M. L. Dahanukar College of Commerce in 1993. He was interested in sports, but started acting after his acting adventures in school and college gave him success and encouragement.<ref name=\"indiatimes1\">{{cite web |url=http://maharashtratimes.indiatimes.com/tv/sameer-chaughule-comedi-chi-bullete-train/articleshow/50230954.cms |title=Sameer Chaughule Comedi chi Bullete Train - Maharashtra Times |website=Maharashtratimes.indiatimes.com |date= |accessdate=15 November 2016}}</ref> After completing his education, Samir worked in [[Mumbai]] and later took a full-time acting career in 2002. Since then has acted in various dramas, TV serials and movies. He is a regular on TV shows such as Maharashtrachi Hasya Jatra and is considered a legend due to his comic timing and acting abilities.\n\nSamir is also a regular contributor to Saamana e-paper under the column 'Fulora' where he writes about the various flavors of life.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://epaper.saamana.com/Details.aspx?id=43523&boxid=34940755 |title=Image view |website=Epaper.saamana.com |access-date=28 June 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Personal Life ==\nSamir is married to Kavita Choughule.\n\n==Filmography==\nSamir has appeared in lead role as well as special appearance in a few Indian movies:\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Year\n!Film\n!Language\n!Role\n!Notes\n|-\n|2005\n|''[[Kaydyacha Bola]]'' \n|Marathi\n|Thambi\n|Special appearance\n|-\n|2008\n|''[[Mumbai Meri Jaan]]''\n|Hindi\n|\n|\n|-\n|2013\n|''[[Aajcha Divas Majha]]''\n|Marathi\n|Satam\n|\n|-\n|2015\n|''[[Vakratunda Mahakaaya]]''\n|Marathi\n|Secretary\n|\n|-\n|2015\n|''[[A Paying Ghost]]''\n|Marathi\n|Ganpule\n|\n|-\n|2016\n|''Mumbai Time'' \n|Marathi\n|\n|\n|-\n|2019\n|[[Vikun Taak]]\n|Marathi\n|\n|\n|}\n\n==Theater work==\nSamir is an actor in Marathi Theater and below are a few plays where he has acted in:\n# ''Asa Mi Asa Mi'' \n# ''Varya Varchi varat'' \n# ''Vyakti Ani Valli'' \n# ''Yada kadachit''\n# ''Chalre Bhoplya Tunuk Tunuk'' \n# ''Balak Palak'' \n# ''Shri Bai Samartha''\n# ''Carry On Heavens'' (Hinglish drama by Bharat Dabholkar)\n# ''Best of Bottoms Up'' (English Drama)\n#Hyancha Kaay Karaaycha\n\n== TV appearances ==\nSamir has also acted in a few TV serials:\n# ''Tikal te Political''  (Political satire by Chandrakant Kulkarni) \n# ''Ambat God''<ref>{{cite web |title=Ambat Goad 4 Days Remaining |date=6 December 2012 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RC9OmokIuEE |website=Youtube.com |accessdate=28 June 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/samir-choughule/credits/900557/ |title=Samir Choughule |website=TVGuide.com |access-date=28 June 2016}}</